{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_446424", "question": "You are tasked with creating a Python program that implements a data structure to represent a list of people, where each person has a name, ID, and email. You should define a struct or class to represent a Person, and then create a method to add a new person to the list. Additionally, you need to implement a method to search for a person by their ID and return their information. The program should be able to handle adding and searching for multiple people.", "answer": "```python\n# Define the Person class to represent a person's information\nclass Person:\n  def __init__(self, name, id, email):\n    self.name = name\n    self.id = id\n    self.email = email\n\n# Create a list to store the people\npeople_list = []\n\n# Method to add a new person to the list\ndef add_person(name, id, email):\n  person = Person(name, id, email)\n  people_list.append(person)\n\n# Method to search for a person by their ID and return their information\ndef search_person_by_id(search_id):\n  for person in people_list:\n    if person.id == search_id:\n      return f\"Name: {person.name}, ID: {person.id}, Email: {person.email}\"\n  return \"Person not found\"\n\n# Add new people to the list\nadd_person(\"Alice\", 1, \"alice@example.com\")\nadd_person(\"Bob\", 2, \"bob@example.com\")\n\n# Search for a person by ID\nprint(search_person_by_id(1))  # Output: Name: Alice, ID: 1, Email: alice@example.com\nprint(search_person_by_id(3))  # Output: Person not found\n```"}
