{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_376944", "question": "Mitch is a freelancer, she works 5 hours every day from Monday to Friday and 3 hours every Saturday and Sunday. If she earns $3 per hour and earns double on weekends, how much does she earn every week?", "answer": "Mitch works 5 hours per day from Monday to Friday, which is a total of 5 days. So, the total hours she works from Monday to Friday is:\n\n5 hours/day * 5 days = 25 hours\n\nShe earns $3 per hour from Monday to Friday, so her earnings for these days are:\n\n25 hours * $3/hour = $75\n\nOn weekends, she works 3 hours each on Saturday and Sunday, which is a total of 2 days. So, the total hours she works on weekends is:\n\n3 hours/day * 2 days = 6 hours\n\nShe earns double on weekends, so her hourly rate on weekends is $3/hour * 2 = $6/hour.\n\nHer earnings for the weekend are:\n\n6 hours * $6/hour = $36\n\nTo find out her total weekly earnings, we add her earnings from weekdays and weekends:\n\n$75 (weekdays) + $36 (weekends) = $111\n\nTherefore, Mitch earns $111 every week."}
