{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1114530", "question": "translate this code from Elixir to python:\n```elixir\ndefmodule Solution do\n  def modify_string(s) do\n    s = String.to_charlist(s)\n    for i <- 0..(length(s) - 1) do\n      if s[i] == \"?\" do\n        for c <- ?a..?z do\n          if (i - 1 < 0 or s[i - 1] != c) and (i + 1 >= length(s) or s[i + 1] != c) do\n            s[i] = c\n            break\n          end\n        end\n      end\n    end\n    String.from_charlist(s)\n  end\nend\n```", "answer": "Pseudocode:\n```\nMODIFY-STRING(S)\n1  n = length(S)\n2  for i = 1 to n\n3      if S[i] == '?'\n4          for c = 'a' to 'z'\n5              if (i - 1 < 0 or S[i - 1] != c) and (i + 1 >= n or S[i + 1] != c)\n6                  S[i] = c\n7                  break\n8  return S\n```\n\n Code\n```python\ndef modifyString(s: str) -> str:\n    s = list(s)\n    for i in range(len(s)):\n        if s[i] == '?':\n            for c in range(ord('a'), ord('z') + 1):\n                if (i - 1 < 0 or s[i - 1] != chr(c)) and (i + 1 >= len(s) or s[i + 1] != chr(c)):\n                    s[i] = chr(c)\n                    break\n    return ''.join(s)\n```"}
