{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1439648", "question": "The simple interest on a certain sum of money for 2 years at 8% per annum is half the compound interest on Rs. 4000 for 2 years at a certain rate per annum. The sum placed on simple interest is Rs. 2625.0000000000027. What is the rate of compound interest per annum?", "answer": "Let's denote the rate of compound interest per annum as R%.\n\nGiven that the simple interest (SI) on a certain sum of money for 2 years at 8% per annum is half the compound interest (CI) on Rs. 4000 for 2 years at R% per annum.\n\nThe formula for simple interest is:\n\\[ SI = \\frac{P \\times r \\times t}{100} \\]\nwhere P is the principal amount, r is the rate of interest per annum, and t is the time period in years.\n\nFor the given sum of Rs. 2625 at 8% per annum for 2 years, the simple interest is:\n\\[ SI = \\frac{2625 \\times 8 \\times 2}{100} \\]\n\\[ SI = \\frac{2625 \\times 16}{100} \\]\n\\[ SI = 2625 \\times 0.16 \\]\n\\[ SI = 420 \\]\n\nNow, the compound interest on Rs. 4000 for 2 years at R% per annum is calculated using the formula:\n\\[ CI = P \\left(1 + \\frac{R}{100}\\right)^t - P \\]\nwhere P is the principal amount, R is the rate of interest per annum, and t is the time period in years.\n\nFor Rs. 4000 at R% per annum for 2 years, the compound interest is:\n\\[ CI = 4000 \\left(1 + \\frac{R}{100}\\right)^2 - 4000 \\]\n\nAccording to the problem, the simple interest is half the compound interest, so:\n\\[ 420 = \\frac{1}{2} \\left[4000 \\left(1 + \\frac{R}{100}\\right)^2 - 4000\\right] \\]\n\\[ 840 = 4000 \\left(1 + \\frac{R}{100}\\right)^2 - 4000 \\]\n\\[ 4000 \\left(1 + \\frac{R}{100}\\right)^2 = 4840 \\]\n\\[ \\left(1 + \\frac{R}{100}\\right)^2 = \\frac{4840}{4000} \\]\n\\[ \\left(1 + \\frac{R}{100}\\right)^2 = 1.21 \\]\n\\[ 1 + \\frac{R}{100} = \\sqrt{1.21} \\]\n\\[ 1 + \\frac{R}{100} = 1.1 \\]\n\\[ \\frac{R}{100} = 1.1 - 1 \\]\n\\[ \\frac{R}{100} = 0.1 \\]\n\\[ R = 0.1 \\times 100 \\]\n\\[ R = 10 \\]\n\nTherefore, the rate of compound interest per annum is 10%."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1290657", "question": "3/5 of the mangoes on a mango tree are ripe. If Lindsay eats 60% of the ripe mangoes, calculate the number of ripe mangoes remaining if there were 400 mangoes on the tree to start with.", "answer": "If 3/5 of the mangoes on the tree are ripe, then there are 3/5 x 400 = <<3/5*400=240>>240 ripe mangoes.\nIf Lindsay eats 60% of the ripe mangoes, then she eats 60/100 x 240 = <<60/100*240=144>>144 mangoes.\nThe number of ripe mangoes remaining is 240 - 144 = <<240-144=96>>96.\n#### 96\nThe answer is: 96"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1327802", "question": "It starts raining at 7:00 and pours heavily until its stops at 17:00  on a particular day. On the second day, the rain takes 2 more hours than it took on the first day to stop. On the third day, the rain pours for twice the amount of time it took on the second day. Calculate the total time it was raining in the three days.", "answer": "On the first day, it rained from 7:00 to 17:00, which is a total of 17:00 - 7:00 = 10 hours.\nOn the second day, the rain took 2 more hours than it took on the first day to stop, so it rained for 10 hours + 2 hours = 12 hours.\nOn the third day, the rain poured for twice the amount of time it took on the second day, so it rained for 12 hours x 2 = 24 hours.\nThe total time it was raining in the three days is 10 hours + 12 hours + 24 hours = 46 hours.\n#### 46\nThe answer is: 46"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_179572", "question": "For every black & white cookie that Elsa makes, she has to make the batter, bake the cookies for 15 minutes and then allow to cool.  She then has to dip the cookies in white icing and allow the icing to harden for 30 minutes. Then she has to re-dip them in chocolate icing and allowed to harden for an additional x minutes.  If it takes her 2 hours to make the cookies from start to finish, It takes 45 minutes to make the dough and cool the cookies before she can start dipping them. What is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "To solve this problem, we need to determine the value of x, which represents the additional minutes needed for the chocolate icing to harden.\nLet's break down the information given:\nTime to make the dough and cool the cookies: 45 minutes\nTime to bake the cookies: 15 minutes\nTime to allow the white icing to harden: 30 minutes\nTotal time to make the cookies from start to finish: 2 hours = 2 * 60 = 120 minutes\nWe can set up the equation as follows:\nTime to make the dough and cool the cookies + Time to bake the cookies + Time to allow the white icing to harden + Time to allow the chocolate icing to harden = Total time to make the cookies from start to finish\n45 + 15 + 30 + x = 120\nLet's simplify and solve for x:\n90 + x = 120\nTo isolate x, we subtract 90 from both sides of the equation:\n90 - 90 + x = 120 - 90\nx = 30\nThe value of x is 30.\n#### 30\nThe answer is: 30"}
