{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_242980", "question": "A certain number when divided by 39 leaves a remainder 18. What is the remainder when the same number is divided by 13?", "answer": "Let's call the certain number \"N\". According to the information given, when N is divided by 39, the remainder is 18. This can be expressed as:\n\nN = 39k + 18\n\nwhere k is some integer representing the quotient when N is divided by 39.\n\nNow, we want to find the remainder when N is divided by 13. Since 39 is a multiple of 13 (39 = 3 * 13), we can express the number 39k as a multiple of 13 as well:\n\n39k = (3 * 13)k = 13(3k)\n\nNow, let's substitute 39k with 13(3k) in the expression for N:\n\nN = 13(3k) + 18\n\nWhen we divide N by 13, the term 13(3k) will be completely divisible by 13, leaving no remainder. Therefore, the remainder when N is divided by 13 will be the same as the remainder when 18 is divided by 13.\n\n18 divided by 13 gives a quotient of 1 and a remainder of 5. Therefore, the remainder when the same number N is divided by 13 is 5."}
