{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_14753", "question": "The manager of a produce market purchased a quantity of tomatoes for $0.80 per pound. Due to improper handling, some percentage of the tomatoes, by weight, were ruined and discarded. The manager wishes to make a profit on the sale of the remaining tomatoes equal to 8 percent of the cost of the tomatoes. She should sell the remaining tomatoes at $1.08 per pound. What percentage of the tomatoes were ruined and discarded?", "answer": "Let's denote the original quantity of tomatoes purchased as \\( Q \\) pounds, and the percentage of tomatoes ruined and discarded as \\( P \\). The cost of the tomatoes is \\( 0.80Q \\) dollars.\n\nThe manager wants to make a profit equal to 8 percent of the cost, which is \\( 0.08 \\times 0.80Q = 0.064Q \\) dollars.\n\nThe remaining tomatoes, which is \\( (1 - P)Q \\) pounds, are to be sold at $1.08 per pound to achieve this profit. So, the revenue from selling the remaining tomatoes is \\( 1.08(1 - P)Q \\) dollars.\n\nThe profit is the revenue minus the cost, so we have:\n\\[ 1.08(1 - P)Q - 0.80Q = 0.064Q \\]\n\nDivide both sides by \\( Q \\) to simplify:\n\\[ 1.08(1 - P) - 0.80 = 0.064 \\]\n\nNow, distribute the 1.08:\n\\[ 1.08 - 1.08P - 0.80 = 0.064 \\]\n\nCombine like terms:\n\\[ 0.28 - 1.08P = 0.064 \\]\n\nSubtract 0.28 from both sides:\n\\[ -1.08P = 0.064 - 0.28 \\]\n\n\\[ -1.08P = -0.216 \\]\n\nNow, divide both sides by -1.08 to solve for \\( P \\):\n\\[ P = \\frac{-0.216}{-1.08} \\]\n\n\\[ P = 0.2 \\]\n\nSo, the percentage of the tomatoes that were ruined and discarded is \\( 0.2 \\) or \\( 20\\% \\)."}
