{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_486026", "question": "def count_backward(steps):\n    \"\"\"\n    A dancer wants to count backward from a given number of steps. However, if the dancer reaches a number divisible by 3, \n    they want to stop counting and perform a spin move instead. Fill in the missing parts of the code to implement this behavior.\n\n    Args:\n    steps (int): The number of steps to count backward from.\n\n    Returns:\n    str: A string representation of the count and spin moves performed by the dancer.\n\n    Example:\n    count_backward(9) -> '9 8 Spin 6 5 Spin 3 2 Spin 0'\n    \"\"\"", "answer": "count = steps\n    moves = []\n\n    while count >= 0:\n        if count % 3 == 0 and count != steps:\n            moves.append(\"Spin\")\n        else:\n            moves.append(str(count))\n        count -= 1\n\n    return ' '.join(moves)"}
