{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_385263", "question": "John has a sneezing fit for 4 minutes. He sneezes once every 2 seconds. How many times does he sneeze?", "answer": "To find out how many times John sneezes, we need to calculate the total number of sneezes in 4 minutes. \n\nFirst, we convert the 4 minutes into seconds:\n4 minutes = 4 x 60 seconds/minute = 240 seconds\n\nSince John sneezes once every 2 seconds, we divide the total number of seconds by the sneeze interval:\n240 seconds / 2 seconds/sneeze = 120 sneezes\n\nTherefore, John sneezes 120 times during his 4-minute sneezing fit."}
