{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_121726", "question": "Before work, Hayden spends 5 minutes ironing his button-up shirt and 3 minutes ironing his pants.  He does this x days a week. He irons over 4 weeks for 160 minutes. What is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "To solve this problem, we need to determine the value of x, which represents the number of days Hayden irons his clothes each week.\nLet's break down the information given:\nTime spent ironing the button-up shirt per day: 5 minutes\nTime spent ironing the pants per day: 3 minutes\nNumber of weeks: 4\nTotal time spent ironing: 160 minutes\nWe can set up the equation as follows:\n(Time spent ironing the button-up shirt per day + Time spent ironing the pants per day) * Number of days per week * Number of weeks = Total time spent ironing\n(5 + 3) * x * 4 = 160\nLet's simplify and solve for x:\n8 * x * 4 = 160\n32x = 160\nTo isolate x, we divide both sides of the equation by 32:\n32x / 32 = 160 / 32\nx = 5\nThe value of x is 5.\n#### 5\nThe answer is: 5"}
