{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_457366", "question": "Katrina has 120 cookies to sell at her bakery. She plans to take home any cookies she doesn’t sell by the end of the day. In the morning, she sells 3 dozen cookies. During the lunch rush, she sells 57 cookies. In the afternoon, she sells x more cookies. She has 11 cookies left to take home. What is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "To solve this problem, we need to determine the value of x, which represents the number of cookies Katrina sold in the afternoon.\nLet's break down the information given:\nNumber of cookies sold in the morning: 3 dozen = 3 * 12 = 36 cookies\nNumber of cookies sold during the lunch rush: 57 cookies\nNumber of cookies sold in the afternoon: x\nNumber of cookies Katrina has left to take home: 11 cookies\nTotal number of cookies Katrina had: 120 cookies\nWe can set up the equation as follows:\nNumber of cookies sold in the morning + Number of cookies sold during the lunch rush + Number of cookies sold in the afternoon + Number of cookies Katrina has left = Total number of cookies Katrina had\n36 + 57 + x + 11 = 120\nLet's simplify and solve for x:\n104 + x = 120\nTo isolate x, we subtract 104 from both sides of the equation:\n104 + x - 104 = 120 - 104\nx = 16\nThe value of x is 16.\n#### 16\nThe answer is: 16"}
