{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1243047", "question": "A line segment begins at $(1, 3)$. It is 5 units long and ends at the point $(4, x)$ and $x > 0$. What is the value of $x$?", "answer": "The distance between the points $(1, 3)$ and $(4, x)$ is $\\sqrt{(4-1)^2 + (x-3)^2} = \\sqrt{9 + (x-3)^2}$.\nSince the line segment is 5 units long, we have $\\sqrt{9 + (x-3)^2} = 5$.\nSquaring both sides of the equation, we get $9 + (x-3)^2 = 25$.\nSubtracting 9 from both sides, we have $(x-3)^2 = 16$.\nTaking the square root of both sides, we get $x-3 = \\pm 4$.\nSolving for $x$, we have $x = 3 \\pm 4$.\nSince $x > 0$, we have $x = \\boxed{7}$.\nThe answer is: 7"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1049751", "question": "Given that $(x + y)^2 = 1$ and $xy = -4$, what is the value of $x^2 + y^2$?", "answer": "Expanding $(x + y)^2$, we get $x^2 + 2xy + y^2 = 1$.\nWe are given that $xy = -4$.\nSubstituting this into the equation, we have $x^2 + 2(-4) + y^2 = 1$.\nSimplifying, we get $x^2 + y^2 = 1 + 8 = \\boxed{9}$.\nThe answer is: 9"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_902775", "question": "How can I create a Ruby on Rails API application to manage a blog with endpoints to create, update, delete, and list all posts?", "answer": "You can create a Ruby on Rails API application to manage a blog by following these steps:\n\n1. Create a new Rails application:\n```bash\nrails new blog_api\n```\n\n2. Define the routes for the API endpoints in the `config/routes.rb` file:\n```ruby\nRails.application.routes.draw do\n  resources :posts, only: [:create, :update, :destroy, :index]\nend\n```\n\n3. Generate the `PostsController` by running the following command:\n```bash\nrails generate controller Posts\n```\n\n4. Open the generated `app/controllers/posts_controller.rb` file and update it with the following code:\n```ruby\nclass PostsController < ApplicationController\n  def index\n    @posts = Post.all\n    render json: @posts\n  end\n\n  def create\n    @post = Post.create!(post_params)\n    render json: @post\n  end\n\n  def update\n    @post = Post.find(params[:id])\n    @post.update_attributes!(post_params)\n    render json: @post\n  end\n\n  def destroy\n    @post = Post.find(params[:id])\n    @post.destroy\n    render json: { message: 'Post deleted' }\n  end\n\n  private\n\n  def post_params\n    params.require(:post).permit(:title, :content)\n  end\nend\n```\n\n5. Create the `Post` model by running the following command:\n```bash\nrails generate model Post title:string content:text\n```\n\n6. Run the database migration to create the `posts` table:\n```bash\nrails db:migrate\n```\n\n7. Your Ruby on Rails API application to manage a blog is now ready. You can start the server by running:\n```bash\nrails server\n```\n\nNow you can make API requests to the following endpoints:\n- `POST /posts` to create a new post\n- `PUT /posts/:id` to update an existing post\n- `DELETE /posts/:id` to delete a post\n- `GET /posts` to list all posts"}
