{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1091256", "question": "You are tasked with implementing the predator-prey equations, also known as the Lotka-Volterra equations, which describe the dynamics of two interacting species in an ecosystem in terms of non-linear differential equations. The two interacting time-dependent observables are the number of prey and the number of predators, both represented as real numbers for the benefit of using differential equations. The two coupled equations for prey and predators are as follows:\n\n𝒟(prey) = (prey-growth-rate × prey) - (predation-rate × predators × prey)\n𝒟(predators) = (predator-growth-rate × predators × prey) - (predator-loss-rate × predators)\n\nThese equations are based on a few assumptions:\n1. In the absence of predators, the prey exhibits exponential growth described by prey-growth-rate.\n2. The number of prey decreases by predation, which is predation-rate times the number of encounters between individuals of each species.\n3. In the absence of prey, the number of predators decreases by starvation, described by predator-loss-rate.\n4. The number of predators grows with the availability of food, which is proportional to both prey and predators with the proportionality constant predator-growth-rate.\n\nImplement a program that takes the initial values of prey and predators, along with the values of prey-growth-rate, predation-rate, predator-growth-rate, and predator-loss-rate, and computes the dynamics of the prey and predator populations over time using the given differential equations.", "answer": "```python\nimport numpy as np\nimport matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n\ndef predator_prey_dynamics(prey_0, predators_0, prey_growth_rate, predation_rate, predator_growth_rate, predator_loss_rate, time_interval):\n    time_points = np.linspace(0, time_interval, 1000)\n    prey = np.zeros(len(time_points))\n    predators = np.zeros(len(time_points))\n    prey[0] = prey_0\n    predators[0] = predators_0\n\n    for i in range(1, len(time_points)):\n        dpdt = (prey_growth_rate * prey[i-1]) - (predation_rate * predators[i-1] * prey[i-1])\n        dcdt = (predator_growth_rate * predators[i-1] * prey[i-1]) - (predator_loss_rate * predators[i-1])\n        prey[i] = prey[i-1] + dpdt * (time_interval/1000)\n        predators[i] = predators[i-1] + dcdt * (time_interval/1000)\n\n    plt.plot(time_points, prey, label='Prey')\n    plt.plot(time_points, predators, label='Predators')\n    plt.xlabel('Time')\n    plt.ylabel('Population')\n    plt.title('Predator-Prey Dynamics')\n    plt.legend()\n    plt.show()\n\n# Example usage\npredator_prey_dynamics(10, 5, 0.1, 0.02, 0.005, 0.1, 10)\n```"}
