{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1380022", "question": "A regular polygon has interior angles of 162 degrees. How many sides does the polygon have?", "answer": "In a regular polygon with $n$ sides, each interior angle is given by the formula $\\frac{(n-2) \\cdot 180}{n}$.\nWe can set up the equation $\\frac{(n-2) \\cdot 180}{n} = 162$ and solve for $n$.\nMultiplying both sides by $n$ gives $(n-2) \\cdot 180 = 162n$.\nExpanding and rearranging gives $180n - 360 = 162n$.\nSubtracting $162n$ from both sides gives $18n - 360 = 0$.\nAdding 360 to both sides gives $18n = 360$.\nDividing both sides by 18 gives $n = \\boxed{20}$.\nThe answer is: 20"}
