{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1178027", "question": "There are 3414 yellow balloons and there are x more black balloons than yellow balloons. If the balloons will be evenly divided among 10 schools, how many balloons will one school receive?\nIf we know the answer to the above question is 859, what is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "There are 3414 yellow balloons.\nThere are x more black balloons than yellow balloons, which means there are 3414 + x black balloons.\nThe total number of balloons is the sum of the yellow and black balloons: 3414 + (3414 + x) = 6828 + x.\nIf the balloons will be evenly divided among 10 schools, each school will receive (6828 + x) / 10 balloons.\nWe are given that each school will receive 859 balloons, so we can write: (6828 + x) / 10 = 859.\nMultiplying both sides by 10, we get: 6828 + x = 8590.\nSubtracting 6828 from both sides, we get: x = 1762.\nThe value of x is 1762.\n#### 1762\nThe answer is: 1762"}
