{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_205796", "question": "What is the positive difference between the $2000^{\\mathrm{th}}$ term and the $2005^{\\mathrm{th}}$ term of the arithmetic sequence $-8,$ $-2,$ $4,$ $10,$ $\\ldots$?", "answer": "The common difference of this arithmetic sequence is $-2 - (-8) = 6$.\nThe $n$th term of the sequence is $a_1 + (n-1)d$, where $a_1$ is the first term and $d$ is the common difference.\nSo, the $2000$th term is $-8 + (2000-1)(6) = -8 + 11994 = 11986$.\nSimilarly, the $2005$th term is $-8 + (2005-1)(6) = -8 + 12024 = 12016$.\nThe positive difference between these two terms is $12016 - 11986 = \\boxed{30}$.\nThe answer is: 30"}
