{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_469346", "question": "Create a Java function that takes in two integers as parameters and returns their sum as a double. The function should also check if the sum exceeds a certain threshold, which is defined as the maximum value of a long integer. If the sum exceeds the threshold, the function should throw an exception with a custom error message indicating the overflow.\n\nAdditionally, the function should implement a custom algorithm for calculating the sum, rather than using the built-in addition operator. The algorithm should utilize bitwise operations to perform the addition operation.\n\nThe function should have a time complexity of O(log n), where n is the larger of the two input integers.", "answer": "Here's a Java function that meets the given requirements:\n\n```java\npublic class Addition {\n    \n    private static final long MAX_VALUE = Long.MAX_VALUE;\n    \n    public static double addWithOverflowCheck(int num1, int num2) {\n        long sum = addUsingBitwise(num1, num2);\n        \n        if (sum > MAX_VALUE) {\n            throw new ArithmeticException(\"Overflow occurred\");\n        }\n        \n        return (double) sum;\n    }\n    \n    private static long addUsingBitwise(int num1, int num2) {\n        long result = 0;\n        int carry = 0;\n        \n        for (int i = 0; i < 32; i++) {\n            int bit1 = (num1 >> i) & 1;\n            int bit2 = (num2 >> i) & 1;\n            \n            // Calculate the sum and carry using bitwise operations\n            int sum = (bit1 ^ bit2) ^ carry;\n            carry = (bit1 & bit2) | (carry & (bit1 ^ bit2));\n            \n            // Update the result using bitwise operations\n            result |= (sum << i);\n        }\n        \n        return result;\n    }\n    \n    public static void main(String[] args) {\n        int num1 = 123456789;\n        int num2 = 987654321;\n        \n        try {\n            double sum = addWithOverflowCheck(num1, num2);\n            System.out.println(\"Sum: \" + sum);\n        } catch (ArithmeticException e) {\n            System.out.println(e.getMessage());\n        }\n    }\n}\n```\n\nThis function uses bitwise operations to calculate the sum of two integers. It iterates over each bit position (up to 32 bits) and performs the addition using XOR and AND operations. The carry is calculated based on the current bit positions of both numbers. The result is updated using OR operations.\n\nThe function `addWithOverflowCheck` takes two integers as input and calls the `addUsingBitwise` function to calculate their sum. It then checks if the sum exceeds the threshold defined as the maximum value of a long integer. If it does, an `ArithmeticException` is thrown with a custom error message indicating the overflow. Otherwise, the sum is returned as a double.\n\nIn the `main` method, you can test the function by providing two integers as input and printing the result. If an overflow occurs, the exception message will be printed instead."}
