{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_294042", "question": "if 35 % of the 880 students at a certain college are enrolled in biology classes , how many students at the college are not enrolled in a biology class ?", "answer": "To find out how many students are not enrolled in a biology class, we first need to calculate how many students are enrolled in biology classes.\n\n35% of 880 students are enrolled in biology classes, so we calculate:\n\n35/100 * 880 = 0.35 * 880 = 308 students\n\nNow, to find out how many students are not enrolled in a biology class, we subtract the number of students enrolled in biology classes from the total number of students:\n\n880 - 308 = 572 students\n\nTherefore, 572 students at the college are not enrolled in a biology class."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1359907", "question": "Harkamal purchased 8 kg of grapes at a certain rate per kg and 9 kg of mangoes at the rate of 60 per kg. He paid 1100 to the shopkeeper. What was the rate of grapes per kg?", "answer": "Let's denote the rate of grapes per kg as \\( G \\) rupees.\n\nHarkamal purchased 8 kg of grapes, so the total cost for the grapes is \\( 8G \\) rupees.\n\nHe also purchased 9 kg of mangoes at the rate of 60 rupees per kg, so the total cost for the mangoes is \\( 9 \\times 60 \\) rupees.\n\nThe total amount paid to the shopkeeper is 1100 rupees, which is the sum of the cost of grapes and mangoes.\n\nSo, we have the equation:\n\n\\( 8G + 9 \\times 60 = 1100 \\)\n\nNow, let's solve for \\( G \\):\n\n\\( 8G + 540 = 1100 \\)\n\nSubtract 540 from both sides:\n\n\\( 8G = 1100 - 540 \\)\n\n\\( 8G = 560 \\)\n\nNow, divide both sides by 8 to find \\( G \\):\n\n\\( G = \\frac{560}{8} \\)\n\n\\( G = 70 \\)\n\nTherefore, the rate of grapes per kg is 70 rupees."}
