{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_610570", "question": "Twenty gremlins and fifteen imps are at the Annual Mischief Convention. The imps have had a lot of in-fighting lately and refuse to shake hands with each other, but they readily shake hands with all of the gremlins. Meanwhile, all the gremlins are quite friendly and shake hands with all of the other gremlins as well as imps. Each pair of creatures shakes hands at most once. How many handshakes were at the convention?", "answer": "To determine the total number of handshakes at the convention given the conditions provided, we need to break down the problem into distinct parts:\n\n1. **Handshakes among Gremlins**:\n   Each gremlin shakes hands with every other gremlin exactly once. The formula to calculate the number of unique handshakes among ( n ) gremlins is:\n   [\n   20 times (20 - 1) / 2\n   ]\n   Hence, the number of handshakes among the gremlins is:\n   [ \n   190 = 20 times (20 - 1) / 2 \n   ]\n   \n2. **Handshakes between Gremlins and Imps**:\n   Each gremlin shakes hands with each imp exactly once, resulting in:\n   [\n   20 times 15\n   ]\n   Thus, the number of handshakes between the gremlins and the imps is:\n   [\n   300 = 20 times 15\n   ]\n\n3. **Total Handshakes Calculation**:\n   The total number of handshakes is the sum of the handshakes among the gremlins and the handshakes between the gremlins and the imps:\n   [\n   490 = 190 + 300\n   ]\n\nUsing this breakdown, if we substitute the variables into the equations and sum the values, we get the final count of handshakes at the convention.\n\nIn mathematical terms:\n[\n490 = left( frac{20 times (20 - 1)}{2} right) + (20 times 15)\n]\n\nThe answer is (490)."}
