{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1301080", "question": "Mr. John works at a shopping mall and receives a monthly income of x, but he spends approximately 5% of this amount on public transport to and from the mall in a month. How much will he have left after deducting his monthly transport fare from his income?\nIf we know the answer to the above question is 1900, what is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "Mr. John's monthly income is x.\nHe spends approximately 5% of this amount on public transport, which means he spends (5/100)*x on transport.\nThe amount he will have left after deducting his transport fare is: x - (5/100)*x = (95/100)*x.\nWe are given that the amount left is 1900, so we can write: (95/100)*x = 1900.\nDividing both sides by (95/100), we get: x = (1900 * 100) / 95.\nCalculating this, we find that x is approximately 2000.\nThe value of x is approximately 2000.\n#### 2000\nThe answer is: 2000"}
