{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_608412", "question": "In a Dictator game, the dictator is given $100 to split with the receiver. If the dictator keeps $40, how much does the receiver get and what is the dictatorial power index in this game?", "answer": "In this Dictator game, if the dictator keeps $40, the receiver gets the remaining amount, which is $100 - $40 = $60.\n\nThe dictatorial power index is the proportion of the total amount that the dictator keeps for themselves. In this case, the dictator keeps $40 out of $100, so the dictatorial power index is:\n\nDictatorial Power Index = (Amount kept by dictator) / (Total amount)\n                                     = $40 / $100\n                                     = 0.4 or 40%\n\nSo, the dictatorial power index in this game is 40%."}
