{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_903094", "question": "心理学者如何诊断人格障碍？", "answer": "人格障碍是一种影响个体社交、情感和认知功能的心理障碍，通常是长期存在的。心理学者通过不同的方法来诊断人格障碍，取决于病人的症状和严重程度。以下是一些心理学家用来诊断人格障碍的通用方法：\n1. 个人访谈：个人访谈包括与患者进行问答式对话，以了解个体的个性特征、行为和心理状况。心理学者可能会询问患者的情感、行为、人际关系和日常生活方面的问题。\n2. 症状评估：症状评估是一种用来确定患者是否出现特定症状的测试工具。这些测试通常会包含一系列的问题或陈述，患者需要回答是否存在某种行为或感觉。这些测试的结果通常在判断患者是否有人格障碍时发挥重要作用。\n3. 行为观察：行为观察是通过观察患者的行为和情绪来确定患者是否有人格障碍。观察者可能会注意到患者反应强烈或冷漠、行为不稳定、情感不稳定或过于敏感等不正常的行为。\n4. 匿名自我评估问卷：匿名自我评估问卷是一种心理学家用来评估患者人格特征的自我报告测试。这些测试通常会包括一系列问题，患者根据自己的感受和行为回答这些问题。\n5. 经典诊断标准：经典诊断标准是一种基于特定症状和表现的指南，心理学家可以使用这些准则来诊断人格障碍。 比如，DSM-5（精神障碍诊断与统计手册第五版）和ICD-10（疾病和有关健康问题的国际统计分类第十版）就是经典诊断标准。\n总之，通过个人访谈、症状评估、行为观察、匿名自我评估问卷、经典诊断标准等方式，心理学家可以确定是否有人格障碍并评估其类型、严重程度和处置方式。在诊断人格障碍的过程中，同时也需要注意到患者的背景、文化和社交环境等因素，以确保诊断结果的准确性和可靠性。"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_734178", "question": ". There are 8 men and 10 women and you need to form a committee of 5 men and 6 women. In how many ways can the committee be formed?\nAnswer Choices: (A) 10420 (B) 11 (C) 11760 (D) 11640 (E) None of these", "answer": "Let's reason about the multi-choice question.\nWe need to select 5 men from 8 men and 6 women from 10 women\nNumber of ways to do this\n= 8C5 × 10C6\n= 8C3 × 10C4 [∵ nCr = nC(n-r)]\n=((8×7×6)/(3×2×1))*((10×9×8*7)/(4×3×2×1))\n=56×210\n=11760\nThe answer is C"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1409905", "question": "Write a story where Helbrecht (Warhammer 40k), Morgan Blackhand, Pagan Min and Shay Cormac are working at IKEA. Add Dialogue. Go Into Detail. Make It Long. Be Creative And Original.", "answer": "In the vast retail space of IKEA, amongst the labyrinthine walkways lined with flat-pack furniture and Swedish meatballs, a peculiar team found their new battlefield. High Marshal Helbrecht of the Black Templars Space Marine Chapter, begrudgingly wearing the standard blue and yellow IKEA uniform over his black power armor, towered over everyone else. Beside him, clad in the neon glare of practical work attire, was the famed Solo, Morgan Blackhand, his cybernetic arm hidden beneath the fabric. Pagan Min, the eccentric and always impeccably dressed dictator from Kyrat, somehow managed to make the uniform look fashionable, while Shay Cormac, the Assassin-Turned-Templar, adjusted himself to the unusual civilian environment.\n\nThey had been summoned to this plane of existence by an ancient being only known as \"The Manager,\" who, for reasons unknown, had foreseen that this unlikely group would become the most efficient IKEA workforce the world had ever seen. Now they were here, feeling more out of place than a cactus in a snowstorm.\n\nThe day started with Helbrecht's booming voice echoing through the aisles, \"Brothers and Sisters of IKEA, we march through these corridors not to face the xenos but to combat customer dissatisfaction and the woe of missing screws! To your stations!\"\n\nMorgan sighed, looking around at the flat-pack furniture fortress, \"Never thought I'd be putting my tactical skills to use in a place like this, but hey, everybody needs a good shelf.\" He flexed his cyber arm, ready for the challenge.\n\nPagan chuckled as he adjusted a scarf that somehow still complemented his uniform. \"Darlings, let's just focus on making this place look more fabulous, shall we? The customers should feel like they're shopping in a palace.\"\n\nShay, meanwhile, had taken to the task like a duck to water, disappearing and reappearing between the aisles with a smoothness born from his former life in stealth, \"Just like being back on the ship,\" he murmured, \"except the sea is a flood of customers, and my shipmates...quite unique.\"\n\nTheir first challenge came in the form of a family uncertain about their choice of a BILLY bookcase.\n\n\"But dear, will this match with our living room?\" asked the woman, her face creased in worry.\n\n\"Madam.\" Helbrecht stepped forward, the floor nearly trembling under his weight. \"The BILLY bookcase is the bastion of lore storage. Its shelves will hold under the weight of tomes unlike any fortress in the Imperium. I assure you, your texts will be well-kept.\"\n\nThe woman blinked, taken aback but clearly reassured by the conviction in his voice. \"Well, I... thank you, sir.\"\n\nMorgan escorted the family to the checkout, offering practical advice on assembly, \"Use a drill with a torque setting—don't strip your screws.\"\n\nPagan, dressing a display model kitchen like a stage for a dramatic play, caught sight of Helbrecht. \"Darling, you left them awestruck,\" he laughed, “But maybe leave out the war references next time?\"\n\nMeanwhile, Shay skillfully detected and approached a customer who was covertly trying to open a sealed flat-pack to check the contents. \"We have display models for that, sir,\" Shay said calmly. \"Let me show you.\"\n\nThe day wore on, mixing the mundane with the unexpected—Morgan defused a tussle over the last FRIHETEN sofa bed with his Solo negotiation skills, Pagan diplomatically upsold kitchen fittings, Shay swiftly attended to lost children, reuniting them with parents, and Helbrecht single-handedly rearranged the entire PAX wardrobe display to the awe of onlookers.\n\nDuring their break, in the shadowy quiet of the staff room, the four sat around, feasting on meatballs and lingonberry juice, exchanging stories of their past glories and the oddity of their present circumstances.\n\nMorgan eyed Helbrecht's armor as he sat awkwardly on the small chair. \"Bet you never thought you'd end up selling furniture when you were crusading across the galaxy.\"\n\nHelbrecht snorted. \"The Emperor works in mysterious ways; if this is my current crusade, I shall not falter. Though I could do without the tiny pencils.\"\n\nShay laughed softly, \"You think this is strange, I went from sailing the North Atlantic to hunting Assassins. And now, I'm helping people choose curtains. Life's funny.\"\n\nPagan, ever the optimist, raised his glass, \"Here's to our strange fates, gentlemen. May we sell these tables and chairs with the same fervor as our previous callings.\"\n\nTheir camaraderie, formed in the crucible of shared bewilderment, grew stronger as the day progressed. By the time \"The Manager\" called day's end, the quartet retired from their positions, not as disgruntled employees but as warriors who had conquered yet another foreign land.\n\nUnbeknownst to them, \"The Manager\"—a being of enigmatic origins—observed from the shadows, smiling. They had indeed become the most efficient and eccentric IKEA workforce in existence, and certainly the most memorable. For the customers who witnessed their service on that fateful day, the tale of Helbrecht, Morgan, Pagan, and Shay at IKEA would live on—an unlikely saga of retail heroism in the most unexpected of theaters."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_908734", "question": "Let $f(x)=2x^4+x^3+x^2-3x+r$. For what value of $r$ is $f(2)=0$?", "answer": "We substitute $x=2$ into the expression for $f(x)$ to get $f(2)=2(2)^4+(2)^3+(2)^2-3(2)+r=32+8+4-6+r=38+r$.\nWe want $f(2)=0$, so $38+r=0$ and $r=\\boxed{-38}$.\nThe answer is: -38"}
