{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_859993", "question": "The epic poem currently contains x lines. If a person adds 3 lines to the poem every month, The poem will contain 90 lines in 22 months. What is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "To solve this problem, we need to determine the value of x, which represents the initial number of lines in the epic poem.\nWe know that 3 lines are added to the poem every month and that the poem will contain 90 lines in 22 months.\nWe can set up the equation as follows:\nInitial number of lines + (Number of months * Number of lines added per month) = Total number of lines\nx + (22 * 3) = 90\nLet's simplify and solve for x:\nx + 66 = 90\nTo isolate x, we subtract 66 from both sides of the equation:\nx + 66 - 66 = 90 - 66\nx = 24\nThe value of x is 24.\n#### 24\nThe answer is: 24"}
