{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_571387", "question": "Find the length of the second side of a triangle if the other two sides measure 7 centimeters and 15 centimeters, and the perimeter of the triangle is 32 centimeters.", "answer": "To find the length of the second side of the triangle, we can use the perimeter formula for a triangle, which is the sum of the lengths of all three sides.\n\nLet's denote the length of the second side as x. According to the problem, we have two sides with lengths 7 cm and 15 cm, and the perimeter is 32 cm.\n\nSo, the equation for the perimeter of the triangle is:\n\n7 + 15 + x = 32\n\nNow, we can solve for x:\n\n22 + x = 32\nx = 32 - 22\nx = 10\n\nTherefore, the length of the second side of the triangle is 10 centimeters."}
