{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1131027", "question": "Jane's quiz scores were X, 97, 92, 85 and 93. What was her mean score?\nIf we know the answer to the above question is 93, what is the value of unknown variable X?", "answer": "We want to find the value of X in the given situation.\nThe mean score can be found by summing all the scores and dividing by the total count.\nWe are given the scores X, 97, 92, 85, and 93.\nThe mean score is:\n(mean score) = (X + 97 + 92 + 85 + 93) / 5\nWe are given that the mean score is 93, so we can write:\n93 = (X + 97 + 92 + 85 + 93) / 5\nMultiplying both sides of the equation by 5, we get:\n465 = X + 97 + 92 + 85 + 93\nSimplifying, we have:\n465 = X + 367\nSubtracting 367 from both sides of the equation, we find:\n98 = X\nThe value of X is 98.\nThe answer is: 98"}
