{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_732082", "question": "How would you limit the output of a SQL query to the first 10 rows, only considering the rows with an even ID?", "answer": "To limit the output of a SQL query to the first 10 rows, only considering the rows with an even ID, you can use the following query:\n\n```sql\nSELECT * FROM your_table\nWHERE MOD(id, 2) = 0\nLIMIT 10;\n```\n\nIn this query, `your_table` represents the name of your table, and `id` represents the column containing the IDs. The `MOD(id, 2) = 0` condition checks if the ID is even (divisible by 2 with no remainder). The `LIMIT 10` clause ensures that only the first 10 rows meeting the condition are returned in the output."}
