{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1113451", "question": "Each edge length of a rectangular solid is a prime number. If the volume of the rectangular solid is 385 cubic units, what is the total surface area, in square units, of the rectangular solid?", "answer": "The prime factors of 385 are 5, 7, and 11, so the dimensions of the rectangular solid are 5, 7, and 11.\nThe surface area of a rectangular solid with dimensions $l,$ $w,$ and $h$ is $2lw + 2lh + 2wh$.\nSo, the surface area of this rectangular solid is $2(5)(7) + 2(5)(11) + 2(7)(11) = 70 + 110 + 154 = \\boxed{334}$ square units.\nThe answer is: 334"}
