{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1376569", "question": "You are tasked with creating a program that parses and extracts metadata information from a given PHP script's comment block. The metadata includes the author's name, email, copyright years, license, version, link, and any additional notes. The comment block is formatted as follows:\n\n```php\n/**\n * @author     <NAME> <<EMAIL>>\n * @copyright  2014-2019 Diemen Design\n * @license    http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT  MIT License\n * @version    0.1.3\n * @link       https://github.com/DiemenDesign/AuroraCMS\n * @notes      This PHP Script is designed to be executed using PHP 7+\n */\n```\n\nYour program should be able to extract the metadata information and store it in a structured format for further processing.\n\nWrite a function or program that takes a PHP script as input and returns a dictionary, map, or object containing the extracted metadata information.\n\nFor example, given the above comment block, the program should return the following dictionary:\n\n```json\n{\n  \"author\": \"<NAME> <<EMAIL>>\",\n  \"copyright\": \"2014-2019 Diemen Design\",\n  \"license\": \"http://opensource.org/licenses/MIT  MIT License\",\n  \"version\": \"0.1.3\",\n  \"link\": \"https://github.com/DiemenDesign/AuroraCMS\",\n  \"notes\": \"This PHP Script is designed to be executed using PHP 7+\"\n}\n```\n\nEnsure that your program can handle various formats of the comment block and extract the metadata accurately.", "answer": "```python\nimport re\n\ndef extract_metadata(php_script):\n    metadata = {}\n    comment_block = re.search(r'/\\*\\*(.*?)\\*/', php_script, re.DOTALL)\n    if comment_block:\n        metadata_lines = comment_block.group(1).strip().split('\\n')\n        for line in metadata_lines:\n            match = re.match(r'\\s*\\*\\s*@(\\w+)\\s+(.*)', line)\n            if match:\n                key, value = match.group(1), match.group(2)\n                metadata[key] = value.strip()\n    return metadata\n```\n\nThe `extract_metadata` function uses regular expressions to parse the PHP script and extract the metadata information from the comment block. It searches for the comment block using the `re.search` method, then iterates through each line to extract the key-value pairs using regular expressions. The extracted metadata is stored in a dictionary and returned as the output."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_373161", "question": "def find_fire_in_building(building_floor):\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a building floor represented as a list of tuples,\n    where each tuple represents the location of a room in the floor.\n    Each room can be empty or contain a fire (represented by True or False).\n    \n    You are a firefighter and your task is to find the first room with a fire in the building floor.\n    \n    Complete the function to find and return the index of the room with a fire if found,\n    otherwise return -1 indicating no fire was found in any room.\n    \n    Hints:\n    - Use nested loops to iterate over the building floor.\n    - Break out of the loops once a room with a fire is found.\n    \n    Example:\n    building_floor = [(False, False), (False, True), (False, False)]\n    find_fire_in_building(building_floor) => 1\n    \"\"\"", "answer": "for floor_index, floor in enumerate(building_floor):\n        for room_index, room in enumerate(floor):\n            if room:\n                return floor_index, room_index  # Returning the indices of the room with fire directly\n    \n    return -1"}
