nt resources to strengthen defenses and develop countermeasures against the relentless onslaught.\n\nYear 10:\nThe planet was now locked in a desperate struggle for survival against the Gotheers. Scientists had managed to study their biology and behavior, discovering their weaknesses but struggling to find efficient ways to exploit them.\n\nYear 15:\nA breakthrough occurred in laboratories worldwide, as scientists developed a specialized compound capable of neutralizing Gotheers' malevolence and weakening their physical strength. Initial tests were promising, and the compound was swiftly deployed in areas most affected by Gotheer attacks.\n\nYear 20:\nHumanity's united efforts, bolstered by the newfound weapon, gradually began to push back against the Gotheers. They no longer possessed their supernatural malevolence, reducing their ability to spread fear at will. However, their incredible speed and agility still posed a significant challenge.\n\nYear 30:\nAfter years of relentless struggle, humanity managed to corner the Gotheers within isolated regions, protected by fortified perimeters. Scientists continued to work tirelessly, looking for a permanent solution to eradicate or control the remaining Gotheer population.\n\nYear 45:\nThe last remaining Gotheers were captured and relocated to secure research facilities. With their malevolence neutralized and under strict human supervision, they became subjects of biological study, unlocking the secrets behind their extraordinary abilities.\n\nYear 50:\nHumanity rebuilt, but the scars of the Gotheer invasion would forever remain. Governments established protocols and facilities to prevent any potential resurgence of such nightmarish creatures. The Gotheers' invasion became a defining period of history, reminding humanity of their vulnerability and the importance of vigilance.\n\nNote: Remember, this timeline is fictional, based on the provided prompt."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1047386", "question": "Ensure the code is adjusted to fit this requirement: \"Fix issue with missing space after replacement\"\nHere are the contents of the file pandoc-figref.py.\n\n```python\n#! /usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Pandoc filter that replaces labels of format {#?:???}, where ? is a\nsingle lower case character defining the type and ??? is an alphanumeric\nlabel, with numbers. Different types are counted separately.\n\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom pandocfilters import toJSONFilter, Str\nimport re\n\nREF_PAT = re.compile('(.*)\\{#([a-z]):(\\w*)\\}(.*)')\n\nknown_labels = {}\n\ndef figref(key, val, fmt, meta):\n    if key == 'Str' and REF_PAT.match(val):\n        start, kind, label, end = REF_PAT.match(val).groups()\n        if kind in known_labels:\n            if label not in known_labels[kind]:\n                known_labels[kind][label] = str(len(known_labels[kind])\\\n                                                + 1)\n        else:\n            known_labels[kind] = {}\n            known_labels[kind][label] = \"1\"\n        return [Str(start)] + [Str(known_labels[kind][label])] + \\\n               [Str(end)]\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    toJSONFilter(figref)\n```", "answer": "```python\n#! /usr/bin/env python3\n\"\"\"Pandoc filter that replaces labels of format {#?:???}, where ? is a\nsingle lower case character defining the type and ??? is an alphanumeric\nlabel, with numbers. Different types are counted separately.\n\n\"\"\"\n\nfrom pandocfilters import toJSONFilter, Str\nimport re\n\nREF_PAT = re.compile('(.*)\\{#([a-z]):(\\w*)\\}(.*)')\n\nknown_labels = {}\n\ndef figref(key, val, fmt, meta):\n    if key == 'Str' and REF_PAT.match(val):\n        start, kind, label, end = REF_PAT.match(val).groups()\n        if kind in known_labels:\n            if label not in known_labels[kind]:\n                known_labels[kind][label] = str(len(known_labels[kind])\\\n                                                + 1)\n        else:\n            known_labels[kind] = {}\n            known_labels[kind][label] = \"1\"\n        return [Str(start)] + [Str(known_labels[kind][label])] + \\\n               [Str(end)] + [Str(\" \")]\n\nif __name__ == '__main__':\n    toJSONFilter(figref)\n```"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_143253", "question": "Colton had 72 dolphin stickers. He gave 4 stickers each to 3 friends.  He also gave his friend Mandy x more than he gave his three friends total.   And he gave Justin 10 less than Mandy.  How many stickers does Colton have left?\nIf we know the answer to the above question is 42, what is the value of unknown variable x?", "answer": "Colton had 72 dolphin stickers.\nHe gave 4 stickers each to 3 friends, so he gave a total of 4 * 3 = 12 stickers to his friends.\nHe also gave Mandy x more than he gave his three friends, so he gave Mandy 12 + x stickers.\nHe gave Justin 10 less than Mandy, so he gave Justin (12 + x) - 10 = 2 + x stickers.\nThe total number of stickers Colton gave to his friends and Mandy is 12 + (12 + x) + (2 + x) = 26 + 2x.\nThe number of stickers Colton has left is 72 - (26 + 2x) = 46 - 2x.\nWe are given that the number of stickers Colton has left is 42, so we can write: 46 - 2x = 42.\nSolving for x, we get: x = 2.\nThe value of x is 2.\n#### 2\nThe answer is: 2"}
