{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_588805", "question": "I need to find all records in a MySQL table where a specific field has a particular value. How can I achieve this using SQL?", "answer": "To retrieve all records in a MySQL table that have a specific value in a certain field, you can use the SQL SELECT statement with a WHERE clause. Here's an example:\n\n```sql\nSELECT * FROM TableName\nWHERE FieldName = 'SpecificValue';\n```\n\nIn this example, replace \"TableName\" with the name of your table and \"FieldName\" with the name of the field you want to check. Also, replace 'SpecificValue' with the specific value you are looking for in that field.\n\nFor instance, if we have a table named \"Customers\" and we want to find all records where the \"State\" field is 'CA', the SQL query would be:\n\n```sql\nSELECT * FROM Customers\nWHERE State = 'CA';\n```\n\nThis query will return all rows from the \"Customers\" table that have 'CA' in the \"State\" field. The asterisk (*) in the SELECT statement represents all columns in the table. However, you can replace it with specific column names if you only need certain fields.\n\nRemember to properly specify your table and field names, and use single quotes around the specific value you are searching for."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_390302", "question": "Danielle bought a new house for $280k. She paid a $40k deposit on the house, and pays the rest using a mortgage that is spread out over 10 years. Danielle makes equal payments every month and at the end of the 10 years, the entire balance will be paid off. How much, in thousands of dollars, does Danielle pay each month?", "answer": "First, we need to calculate the amount Danielle needs to pay through the mortgage. She bought the house for $280k and paid a $40k deposit, so the remaining balance is:\n\n$280k - $40k = $240k\n\nThis $240k will be paid off over 10 years. There are 12 months in a year, so over 10 years, there will be:\n\n10 years * 12 months/year = 120 months\n\nTo find out how much Danielle pays each month, we divide the total mortgage amount by the number of months:\n\n$240k / 120 months = $2k per month\n\nSo, Danielle pays $2k (or $2000) each month."}
