{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_203612", "question": "The average temperature for Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday was 42°C. The average temperature for Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday was 44°C. If the temperature on Friday was 43°C, what was the temperature on Tuesday?", "answer": "Let's denote the temperatures on Tuesday, Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday as T, W, Th, and F, respectively.\n\nAccording to the information given:\n\n(T + W + Th) / 3 = 42°C  (1)\n(W + Th + F) / 3 = 44°C  (2)\n\nWe also know that F = 43°C.\n\nWe can multiply both sides of equation (1) by 3 to get the total sum of temperatures for Tuesday, Wednesday, and Thursday:\n\nT + W + Th = 42°C * 3\nT + W + Th = 126°C  (3)\n\nSimilarly, we can multiply both sides of equation (2) by 3 to get the total sum of temperatures for Wednesday, Thursday, and Friday:\n\nW + Th + F = 44°C * 3\nW + Th + F = 132°C  (4)\n\nNow, we can substitute the value of F into equation (4):\n\nW + Th + 43°C = 132°C\nW + Th = 132°C - 43°C\nW + Th = 89°C  (5)\n\nNow we have two equations with two unknowns (equation 3 and equation 5):\n\nT + W + Th = 126°C  (3)\nW + Th = 89°C  (5)\n\nWe can subtract equation (5) from equation (3) to find the temperature on Tuesday (T):\n\n(T + W + Th) - (W + Th) = 126°C - 89°C\nT = 37°C\n\nSo, the temperature on Tuesday was 37°C."}
