{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_947553", "question": "Jason picked some pears, gave Keith 47 pears, and Mike gave 12 pears from the pear tree to Jason. Jason has 11 pears now. How many pears did Jason pick initially?", "answer": "Let's call the number of pears Jason picked initially P.\n\nAfter giving Keith 47 pears, Jason had P - 47 pears left.\n\nThen Mike gave Jason 12 pears, so Jason had P - 47 + 12 pears.\n\nWe know that after all these transactions, Jason has 11 pears. So we can set up the following equation:\n\nP - 47 + 12 = 11\n\nNow, let's solve for P:\n\nP - 35 = 11\nP = 11 + 35\nP = 46\n\nJason picked 46 pears initially."}
