{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_528169", "question": "def find_common_elements(list1, list2):\n    \"\"\"\n    Given two lists, find the common elements using slicing and the in operator.\n\n    Args:\n    list1 (list): The first list.\n    list2 (list): The second list.\n\n    Returns:\n    list: A new list containing the common elements found in both input lists.\n\n    Example:\n    >>> find_common_elements(['apple', 'banana', 'cherry', 'date'], ['banana', 'apple', 'fig', 'cherry'])\n    ['apple', 'banana', 'cherry']\n    >>> find_common_elements(['cat', 'dog', 'elephant', 'fox'], ['lion', 'elephant', 'kangaroo'])\n    ['elephant']\n    \"\"\"", "answer": "common_elements = []\n    for element in list1:\n        if element in list2:\n            common_elements.append(element)\n    return common_elements"}
