{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_792009", "question": "def find_largest_multiple(divisors, upper_limit):\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of divisors and an upper limit, find the largest multiple of any of the divisors\n    that is less than or equal to the upper limit.\n\n    Args:\n    - divisors (list): A list of integers representing the divisors\n    - upper_limit (int): An integer representing the upper limit\n\n    Returns:\n    - int: The largest multiple of any of the divisors that is less than or equal to the upper limit\n    \"\"\"", "answer": "largest_multiple = 0  # Initialize the largest_multiple variable to 0\n\n    # Iterate over each number from 1 to upper_limit (inclusive)\n    for i in range(1, upper_limit + 1):\n        for divisor in divisors:  # Iterate over each divisor in the list\n            if i % divisor == 0:  # Check if the number is divisible by the divisor\n                largest_multiple = max(largest_multiple, i)  # Update largest_multiple if i is larger\n\n    return largest_multiple  # Return the largest multiple found"}
