{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1292653", "question": "port this code from PHP to python:\n```php\nclass PeekingIterator implements Iterator {\n    private $iterator;\n    private $next_val;\n\n    function __construct($iterator) {\n        $this->iterator = $iterator;\n        $this->next_val = $this->iterator->current();\n    }\n\n    function peek() {\n        return $this->next_val;\n    }\n\n    function next() {\n        $current_val = $this->next_val;\n        $this->iterator->next();\n        $this->next_val = $this->iterator->current();\n        return $current_val;\n    }\n\n    function hasNext() {\n        return ($this->next_val !== null);\n    }\n\n    // Iterator interface methods\n    function current() {\n        return $this->next_val;\n    }\n\n    function key() {\n        return $this->iterator->key();\n    }\n\n    function next() {\n        $this->iterator->next();\n        $this->next_val = $this->iterator->current();\n    }\n\n    function rewind() {\n        $this->iterator->rewind();\n        $this->next_val = $this->iterator->current();\n    }\n\n    function valid() {\n        return ($this->next_val !== null);\n    }\n}\n```", "answer": "Pseudocode:\n```\nPeekingIterator:\n  constructor(iterator)\n    self.iterator = iterator\n    self.next_val = iterator.next()\n\n  peek()\n    return self.next_val\n\n  next()\n    current_val = self.next_val\n    self.next_val = self.iterator.next()\n    return current_val\n\n  hasNext()\n    return self.next_val is not None\n```\n\n Code\n```python\nclass PeekingIterator:\n    def __init__(self, iterator):\n        self.iterator = iterator\n        self.next_val = next(self.iterator, None)\n\n    def peek(self):\n        return self.next_val\n\n    def next(self):\n        current_val = self.next_val\n        self.next_val = next(self.iterator, None)\n        return current_val\n\n    def hasNext(self):\n        return self.next_val is not None\n```"}
