{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1347833", "question": "Haylee is a fish lover and has 5 dozens of guppies. Jose, who has half the guppies as Haylee, also loves fish. Charliz owns guppies, but only one third of what Jose has. Nicolai has four times the number of guppies Charliz has. How many guppies do all of them have together?", "answer": "Haylee has 5 dozen guppies, so in actual number of guppies, she has 5*12=60 guppies. Jose has 0.5 of what Haylee has, so he has 60*0.5=30 guppies. Charliz has 1/3 of what Jose has, so she has 30*1/3=10 guppies. Nicolai has 4 times as many guppies as Charliz, so he has 10*4=40 guppies.\nThe total number of guppies among the four friends is the sum of the guppies each friend has: 60+30+10+40=140.\nThe answer is 140."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_777625", "question": "A washing machine uses 20 gallons of water for a heavy wash, a certain amount of water for a regular wash, and 2 gallons of water for a light wash per load of laundry. If bleach is used, there is an extra light wash cycle added to rinse the laundry thoroughly. There are two heavy washes, three regular washes, and one light wash to do. Two of the loads need to be bleached. The washing machine will need 76 gallons of water. How many gallons of water does the washing machine use for a regular wash?", "answer": "Let's denote the amount of water used for a regular wash as R gallons.\n\nWe know that:\n- A heavy wash uses 20 gallons of water.\n- A light wash uses 2 gallons of water.\n- If bleach is used, an extra light wash cycle is added.\n\nWe have:\n- 2 heavy washes, which will use 2 * 20 = 40 gallons of water.\n- 3 regular washes, which will use 3 * R = 3R gallons of water.\n- 1 light wash, which will use 1 * 2 = 2 gallons of water.\n- 2 loads with bleach, which will add 2 extra light washes, using 2 * 2 = 4 gallons of water.\n\nThe total water usage is 76 gallons, so we can set up the following equation:\n\n40 (heavy washes) + 3R (regular washes) + 2 (light wash) + 4 (bleach light washes) = 76\n\nNow, we can solve for R:\n\n40 + 3R + 2 + 4 = 76\n3R + 46 = 76\n3R = 76 - 46\n3R = 30\nR = 30 / 3\nR = 10\n\nThe washing machine uses 10 gallons of water for a regular wash."}
