{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_50356", "question": "machine a can process 6000 envelopes in 3 hours . machines b and c working together but independently can process the same number of envelopes in 2.5 hours . if machines a and c working together but independently process 3000 envelopes in 1 hour , then how many hours would it take machine b to process 9800 envelopes .", "answer": "Let's denote the rate at which machine A processes envelopes as A, machine B as B, and machine C as C. The rate is in envelopes per hour.\n\nFrom the information given, we know that machine A processes 6000 envelopes in 3 hours, so its rate is:\nA = 6000 envelopes / 3 hours = 2000 envelopes/hour\n\nMachines B and C together process 6000 envelopes in 2.5 hours, so their combined rate is:\nB + C = 6000 envelopes / 2.5 hours = 2400 envelopes/hour\n\nMachines A and C together process 3000 envelopes in 1 hour, so their combined rate is:\nA + C = 3000 envelopes / 1 hour = 3000 envelopes/hour\n\nWe already know the rate of machine A, so we can find the rate of machine C by subtracting the rate of machine A from the combined rate of machines A and C:\nC = (A + C) - A = 3000 envelopes/hour - 2000 envelopes/hour = 1000 envelopes/hour\n\nNow we can find the rate of machine B by subtracting the rate of machine C from the combined rate of machines B and C:\nB = (B + C) - C = 2400 envelopes/hour - 1000 envelopes/hour = 1400 envelopes/hour\n\nNow we want to find out how long it would take machine B to process 9800 envelopes. We can use the rate of machine B to find the time:\nTime = Number of envelopes / Rate of machine B\nTime = 9800 envelopes / 1400 envelopes/hour = 7 hours\n\nSo, it would take machine B 7 hours to process 9800 envelopes."}
