{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_911164", "question": "Two trains are approaching a bridge from opposite sides. Train A is 300 meters long and traveling at 90 km/hr. Train B is 400 meters long and traveling at 100 km/hr. They both start to cross the bridge at the same time. Assuming Train A and Train B take the same amount of time to completely clear the bridge, determine the length of the bridge.", "answer": "Let's denote the length of the bridge as \\( L \\).\n\nSince both trains take the same amount of time to clear the bridge, we can set up an equation based on the fact that time is equal to distance divided by speed.\n\nFor Train A, the total distance it needs to cover to completely clear the bridge is its own length plus the length of the bridge, which is \\( 300 + L \\) meters. The speed of Train A is 90 km/hr, which we need to convert to meters per second to be consistent with the other units. There are 1000 meters in a kilometer and 3600 seconds in an hour, so the speed in meters per second is \\( \\frac{90 \\times 1000}{3600} = 25 \\) m/s.\n\nFor Train B, the total distance it needs to cover to completely clear the bridge is its own length plus the length of the bridge, which is \\( 400 + L \\) meters. The speed of Train B is 100 km/hr, which we convert to meters per second as \\( \\frac{100 \\times 1000}{3600} \\approx 27.78 \\) m/s.\n\nNow we can set up the equations for the time it takes for each train to clear the bridge:\n\nFor Train A: \\( \\text{Time}_A = \\frac{300 + L}{25} \\)\nFor Train B: \\( \\text{Time}_B = \\frac{400 + L}{27.78} \\)\n\nSince \\( \\text{Time}_A = \\text{Time}_B \\), we can set the two equations equal to each other:\n\n\\( \\frac{300 + L}{25} = \\frac{400 + L}{27.78} \\)\n\nNow we solve for \\( L \\):\n\n\\( 27.78(300 + L) = 25(400 + L) \\)\n\\( 8334 + 27.78L = 10000 + 25L \\)\n\\( 27.78L - 25L = 10000 - 8334 \\)\n\\( 2.78L = 1666 \\)\n\\( L = \\frac{1666}{2.78} \\)\n\\( L \\approx 599.28 \\) meters\n\nTherefore, the length of the bridge is approximately 599.28 meters."}
