{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1085204", "question": "A line contains the points $(-1, 6)$, $(6, k)$ and $(20, 3)$. What is the value of $k$?", "answer": "The slope of the line passing through $(-1, 6)$ and $(6, k)$ is $\\frac{k-6}{6-(-1)} = \\frac{k-6}{7}$.\nThe slope of the line passing through $(6, k)$ and $(20, 3)$ is $\\frac{3-k}{20-6} = \\frac{3-k}{14}$.\nSince the two lines are the same line, their slopes are equal, so we have $\\frac{k-6}{7} = \\frac{3-k}{14}$.\nCross-multiplying, we have $2(k-6) = 3-k$, which simplifies to $2k-12=3-k$.\nSolving for $k$, we find $k = \\boxed{\\frac{15}{3} = 5}$.\nThe answer is: 5"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1186443", "question": "Please answer the following question: Build a movie plot around this: What is a name of mission? Day of the Dead\nAnswer:", "answer": "Title: Day of the Dead: Operation Requiem\n\nGenre: Action/Thriller\n\nPlot:\n\nIn the heart of Mexico City, the annual Day of the Dead festival is underway, drawing millions of participants from all over the world. Unbeknownst to the festival-goers, a mysterious and powerful artifact has been hidden in the city's catacombs for centuries. This ancient relic has the power to open a supernatural gateway, allowing the dead to return to the world of the living.\n\nA notorious terrorist organization, The Divine Hand, led by the enigmatic and ruthless leader, General Alistair Mercado, is determined to seize the artifact and unleash chaos on the world. Mercado's carefully woven web of espionage has infiltrated the Mexican government and military, creating a dangerous atmosphere of uncertainty and distrust.\n\nWhen intelligence agencies around the world receive a tip-off about the impending catastrophe, they assemble a multinational team of elite Special Forces operatives named Operation Requiem. This team is the last hope in preventing the artifact from falling into the wrong hands. Their mission: to infiltrate the Day of the Dead festivities, locate and secure the artifact, and eliminate The Divine Hand.\n\nAs the operation commences, the team members find themselves navigating through an increasingly complex and dangerous maze of clues. Meanwhile, they must stay one step ahead of Mercado's ruthless assassins and avoid the suspicion of local law enforcement. To complicate matters further, a rogue Mexican Marine, Lieutenant Sofia Isabella Ruiz, has taken matters into her own hands and is on her personal mission of vengeance against Mercado.\n\nAs the intensity of the Day of the Dead festival reaches its peak, revelations about the true nature of the artifact begin to surface. The team discovers that the relic is actually a remnant of an ancient Aztec civilization that foretold the return of their god of death, Mictlantecuhtli. If the artifact is activated on the Day of the Dead, it would summon this god and cause an unstoppable cataclysm.\n\nIn an action-fueled race against time, Operation Requiem must forge an uneasy alliance with Lieutenant Ruiz as they storm General Mercado's heavily secured stronghold. Just as the final explosive confrontation takes place, the agent entrusted with the artifact faces a life-changing decision: use the artifact's power for the greater good or destroy it and risk the wrath of Mictlantecuhtli.\n\nThe fate of humanity hangs in the balance as Operation Requiem confronts the true meaning of sacrifice, forcing them to redefine their own code of honor and duty. In the ultimate battle of good versus evil, the Day of the Dead will go down in history as the day the world stood on the brink of annihilation, and a small group of heroes banded together to save it."}
