mmand(qInsert, (SqlConnection)dbcon);\n```\n\nBy using the explicit cast, you are indicating to the compiler that the `dbcon` object should be treated as a `SqlConnection`. This will resolve the error you encountered.\n\nAlternatively, you can define `dbcon` as a `SqlConnection` from the beginning. Update the declaration of `dbcon` like this:\n\n```csharp\nSqlConnection dbcon;\n```\n\nThen, you can directly assign `dbcon` to the `SqlCommand.Connection` property without needing to perform any casts. Here's an example:\n\n```csharp\nnew SqlCommand(qInsert, dbcon);\n```\n\nRemember to make the necessary changes in your code based on the approach you choose."}
