{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1328513", "question": "Nathan has a box with two sides each measuring 12 inches by 9 inches, another two sides each measuring 7 inches by 8 inches, and a top and bottom each with an area of 60 square inches. He plans to line the entire interior of the box with velvet. Compute the total square inch area of velvet fabric Nathan needs.", "answer": "The total area to be covered with velvet consists of the areas of the long sides, short sides, and the top and bottom. \n\n1. Calculate the area of the two long sides:\n   The area of one long side is 12 * 9, and since there are two long sides, the total area for the long sides is 12 * 9 * 2 = 216 square inches.\n\n2. Calculate the area of the two short sides:\n   The area of one short side is 7 * 8, and since there are two short sides, the total area for the short sides is 7 * 8 * 2 = 112 square inches.\n\n3. Calculate the total area of the top and bottom:\n   The area of the top and bottom together is 60 * 2 = 120 square inches.\n\n4. Finally, sum up the areas of all sides:\n   The total area of velvet Nathan needs is 216 + 112 + 120 = 448 square inches. \n\nThe answer is 448 square inches."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_861093", "question": "def multiply_selection(numbers):\n    \"\"\"\n    Given a list of numbers, select the odd numbers and multiply them by 2.\n\n    Parameters:\n    numbers (list): A list of integer numbers.\n\n    Returns:\n    list: A list containing the odd numbers multiplied by 2.\n\n    \"\"\"", "answer": "# Select the odd numbers in the list using a list comprehension\n    odd_numbers = [num for num in numbers if num % 2 != 0]\n\n    # Multiply each odd number by 2\n    multiplied_numbers = [odd_num * 2 for odd_num in odd_numbers]\n\n    return multiplied_numbers"}
