{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_192917", "question": "What is the most effective method of cleaning and maintaining contact lenses for daily use?", "answer": "The most effective method of cleaning and maintaining contact lenses for daily use includes the following steps:\n\n1. Wash hands thoroughly with soap and water and dry them with a clean, lint-free towel.\n2. Remove contact lenses from eyes and place them in the palm of your hand.\n3. Apply a few drops of multipurpose solution or saline solution to each lens and rub them gently with your fingertips for 20 seconds.\n4. Rinse the lenses with the solution to remove any debris or dirt.\n5. Place the lenses in a clean and dry case, and fill it with the solution.\n6. Leave the lenses in the solution for at least 6 hours or overnight.\n7. Before wearing the lenses again, rinse them with the solution and then apply them on your eyes.\n8. Don't forget to clean the case with solution and let it air dry, and replace it every three months.\n\nIt is important to follow these steps daily to avoid infections and to prolong the life of your contact lenses."}
