{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_625593", "question": "Write a list comprehension that produces a list of prime numbers from a given list of numbers.\nnumbers = [12,15,18,19,21,22,23,25,27,30]", "answer": "Here is a Python solution for the problem using list comprehension:\n\n```python\ndef is_prime(n):\n    if n < 2:\n        return False\n    for i in range(2, int(n**0.5) + 1):\n        if n % i == 0:\n            return False\n    return True\n\nnumbers = [12,15,18,19,21,22,23,25,27,30]\nprime_numbers = [num for num in numbers if is_prime(num)]\nprint(prime_numbers)  # Output: [19, 23]\n```\n\nIn the code above, the function is_prime checks whether a number is prime or not. Then using list comprehension, we iterate through the given list of numbers and append the number to prime_numbers list only if it is a prime number."}
