{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1158019", "question": "Write a function in JavaScript to extract the Kth highest digit from a given number. The number can be a positive or negative integer. The number will not exceed 10^15 in absolute value and K will be between 1 and the number of digits in the number.\n\nExample:\nInput: \nnumber = -98256473\nK = 3\n\nOutput:\n6\n\nNote:\nIn the given example, the number has 8 digits (-98256473), and the 3rd highest digit is 6.", "answer": "function extractKthHighestDigit(number, K) {\n  // convert number to string\n  var numberStr = Math.abs(number).toString();\n\n  // sort the string in descending order\n  var sortedStr = numberStr.split('').sort(function(a, b) {\n    return b - a;\n  });\n\n  // return the Kth highest digit\n  return parseInt(sortedStr[K - 1]);\n}\n\n// test the function\nconsole.log(extractKthHighestDigit(-98256473, 3)); // 6\nconsole.log(extractKthHighestDigit(98256473, 2)); // 7\nconsole.log(extractKthHighestDigit(0, 1)); // 0\nconsole.log(extractKthHighestDigit(12345, 5)); // 1"}
