{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_118542", "question": "Tom drives from town Q to town B, driving at a constant speed of 60 miles per hour. From town B, Tom immediately continues to town C. The distance between Q and B is twice the distance between B and C. Tom's speed driving from B to C is 20 miles per hour. What is the average speed of the whole journey in miles per hour?", "answer": "Let's denote the distance between town B and town C as \\( D \\). Since the distance between Q and B is twice the distance between B and C, the distance between Q and B is \\( 2D \\).\n\nTom drives from Q to B at a speed of 60 mph. The time it takes to cover this distance is \\( \\frac{2D}{60} \\) hours.\n\nTom then drives from B to C at a speed of 20 mph. The time it takes to cover this distance is \\( \\frac{D}{20} \\) hours.\n\nThe total distance of the journey is \\( 2D + D = 3D \\).\n\nThe total time of the journey is \\( \\frac{2D}{60} + \\frac{D}{20} \\) hours. To combine these, we need a common denominator, which is 60. So we convert \\( \\frac{D}{20} \\) to \\( \\frac{3D}{60} \\).\n\nThe total time is now \\( \\frac{2D}{60} + \\frac{3D}{60} = \\frac{5D}{60} \\) hours.\n\nThe average speed of the whole journey is the total distance divided by the total time:\n\n\\[ \\text{Average speed} = \\frac{\\text{Total distance}}{\\text{Total time}} \\]\n\n\\[ \\text{Average speed} = \\frac{3D}{\\frac{5D}{60}} \\]\n\n\\[ \\text{Average speed} = \\frac{3D}{1} \\times \\frac{60}{5D} \\]\n\n\\[ \\text{Average speed} = 3 \\times 12 \\]\n\n\\[ \\text{Average speed} = 36 \\text{ mph} \\]\n\nSo the average speed of the whole journey is 36 miles per hour."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1460298", "question": "Implement a function in C++ that calculates the factorial of a given integer using recursion.\n5", "answer": "#include <iostream>\nusing namespace std;\n\nint factorial(int n);\n\nint main() {\n    int num = 5;\n    cout << \"Factorial of \" << num << \" is \" << factorial(num) << endl;\n    return 0;}\n\nint factorial(int n) {\n    if (n == 0 || n == 1)\n        return 1;\n    else\n        return n * factorial(n-1);}"}
