{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1467534", "question": "Jeff is collecting matchbox cars. He has a certain number of cars and trucks. He has 60 total vehicles and 20 trucks. What is the ratio of the number of cars to the number of trucks in his collection?", "answer": "If Jeff has 60 total vehicles and 20 of them are trucks, then the number of cars he has would be the total minus the trucks. \n\nNumber of cars = Total vehicles - Number of trucks\nNumber of cars = 60 - 20\nNumber of cars = 40\n\nNow, to find the ratio of the number of cars to the number of trucks:\n\nNumber of cars : Number of trucks = 40 : 20\n\nThis ratio can be simplified by dividing both numbers by the greatest common divisor, which is 20 in this case:\n\n40 ÷ 20 : 20 ÷ 20 = 2 : 1\n\nSo, the ratio of the number of cars to the number of trucks in Jeff's collection is 2:1."}
