{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_181441", "question": "You are tasked with creating a Python class that serves as a handler for a SQLite database. The class should have the following functionalities:\n- Initialize the database connection and create a table if it does not exist, with columns for 'name' and 'expr'\n- Have a method to drop the table if it exists\n- Retrieve all model names from the database\n- Close the database connection\n- Get the values associated with a specific model name\n- Add or update a model name and its associated value\n- Check if a model name exists in the database\n\nCreate a Python class with the above functionalities for handling SQLite databases.", "answer": "```python\nimport sqlite3\n\nclass dbHandler:\n    def __init__(self, path):\n        self.conn = sqlite3.connect(path)\n        self.c = self.conn.cursor()\n        sql = 'CREATE TABLE if not exists models (name text PRIMARY KEY, expr text)'\n        self.c.execute(sql)\n        self.conn.commit()\n        self.get_model_names()\n\n    def drop_table(self):\n        self.c.execute('DROP TABLE if exists models')\n        self.conn.commit()\n\n    def get_model_names(self):\n        self.c.execute('SELECT * FROM models ')\n        rows = self.c.fetchall()\n        self.keys = [r[0] for r in rows]\n        return rows\n\n    def close(self):\n        self.conn.close()\n\n    def get(self, key):\n        self.c.execute('SELECT * FROM models WHERE name=?', (key,))\n        row = self.c.fetchone()\n        return row\n\n    def put(self, key, obj_str):\n        if self.has_key(key):\n            self.c.execute('UPDATE models SET expr=? WHERE name=?', (obj_str, key))\n        else:\n            self.c.execute('INSERT INTO models (name, expr) values (?, ?)', (key, obj_str))\n        self.conn.commit()\n\n    def has_key(self, k):\n        return k in self.keys\n```\nThis solution provides a Python class `dbHandler` that handles SQLite databases with the required functionalities."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_604869", "question": "Jackson's school has a 36 week school year, and he has a varying lunch schedule. On Wednesdays and Fridays, his mom usually packs him a peanut butter and jelly sandwich. There are 2 public holidays that fall on Wednesdays and 3 on Fridays this school year, removing 5 school days from the calculation. Every 4 weeks, Jackson asks his mom to pack him a ham and cheese sandwich instead of a peanut butter and jelly sandwich on 1 Wednesday and 2 Fridays, resulting in 9 weeks where his sandwich choices change. Due to unforeseen circumstances, he misses 1 Wednesday and 2 Fridays altogether throughout the school year. Taking into account the public holidays, the frequency of Jackson's requests for ham and cheese sandwiches, and his absences from school, how many peanut butter and jelly sandwiches did he eat for lunch this school year?", "answer": "Let's break down the calculation step by step:\n\n1. Calculate the total number of Wednesdays and Fridays in the school year:\n- There are 36 weeks in the school year.\n- Each week has 1 Wednesday and 1 Friday, so there are 36 Wednesdays and 36 Fridays.\n\n2. Subtract the public holidays:\n- There are 2 public holidays on Wednesdays and 3 on Fridays.\n- This leaves us with 36 - 2 = 34 Wednesdays and 36 - 3 = 33 Fridays.\n\n3. Subtract the days Jackson is absent:\n- Jackson misses 1 Wednesday and 2 Fridays.\n- This leaves us with 34 - 1 = 33 Wednesdays and 33 - 2 = 31 Fridays.\n\n4. Calculate the days Jackson asks for a ham and cheese sandwich:\n- Every 4 weeks, he asks for a ham and cheese sandwich on 1 Wednesday and 2 Fridays.\n- There are 36 weeks in the school year, so this happens 36 / 4 = 9 times.\n- This means he asks for a ham and cheese sandwich on 9 Wednesdays and 18 Fridays.\n\n5. Subtract the days Jackson eats a ham and cheese sandwich from the total:\n- For Wednesdays: 33 (remaining Wednesdays after holidays and absences) - 9 (ham and cheese sandwich days) = 24 peanut butter and jelly sandwiches on Wednesdays.\n- For Fridays: 31 (remaining Fridays after holidays and absences) - 18 (ham and cheese sandwich days) = 13 peanut butter and jelly sandwiches on Fridays.\n\n6. Add the total number of peanut butter and jelly sandwiches for Wednesdays and Fridays:\n- 24 (Wednesdays) + 13 (Fridays) = 37 peanut butter and jelly sandwiches in total for the school year."}
