{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_447512", "question": "Devise a Python function that scrupulously scrutinizes a provided list, with the objective of ascertaining if all positions distinguished by their odd numerical order are solely inhabited by elements that exhibit the identical odd numerical property, thereby necessitating a two-step reasoning process: identifying odd indices and verifying the oddness of their corresponding elements.", "answer": "Here is a Python function to achieve your task. We can iterate through the list, checking the elements at odd indices, and returns False if any one of those elements is not odd itself:\n\n```python\ndef check_odd_indices(input_list):\n    # Iterating over the list\n    for i in range(len(input_list)):\n        # Check if index is odd\n        if i % 2 != 0:\n            # Check if element at odd index is not odd\n            if input_list[i] % 2 == 0:\n                return False\n    return True\n```\n\nThis function returns True only if all elements at odd indices are also odd. Otherwise, it returns False."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_930319", "question": "Ben has two brothers. They can each eat 12 slices of pizza. They are ordering pizza for the night and want to make sure they get enough. The large pizzas have 14 slices and the small pizzas have a certain number of slices. If they order 1 small pizza, they need to order 2 large pizzas. How many slices are in a small pizza?", "answer": "Ben has two brothers, so including Ben, there are three people. Each person can eat 12 slices of pizza, so in total, they can eat 3 x 12 = 36 slices of pizza.\n\nIf they order 1 small pizza and 2 large pizzas, the total number of slices should be equal to or greater than 36 slices.\n\nWe know that each large pizza has 14 slices, so 2 large pizzas would have 2 x 14 = 28 slices.\n\nSince they need at least 36 slices in total, we can subtract the number of slices from the large pizzas from the total number of slices they need to find out how many slices the small pizza should have.\n\n36 slices (total needed) - 28 slices (from 2 large pizzas) = 8 slices.\n\nTherefore, the small pizza must have 8 slices."}
