{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1412926", "question": "def print_sum_of_numbers_until_break(num_list):\n    \"\"\"\n    This function takes a list of numbers as input and uses a loop to calculate the sum of the numbers.\n    However, it should break out of the loop when encountering a negative number. The final sum should be returned.\n\n    Args:\n    - num_list: A list of integers\n\n    Returns:\n    - sum_of_numbers: The sum of numbers in the list until a negative number is encountered\n\n    Example:\n    >>> print_sum_of_numbers_until_break([3, 5, 2, -1, 4, -2])\n    10\n    \"\"\"", "answer": "sum_of_numbers = 0\n\n    for num in num_list:\n        if num < 0:\n            break\n        sum_of_numbers += num\n\n    return sum_of_numbers"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_525756", "question": "A tank is filled by 3 pipes A, B, C in 8 hours. Pipe C is twice as fast as B and B is twice as fast as A. How much time will pipe A alone take to fill the tank?", "answer": "Let's denote the rate at which pipe A fills the tank as A (in tanks per hour), the rate for pipe B as B, and the rate for pipe C as C.\n\nAccording to the problem, pipe B is twice as fast as A, so B = 2A. Similarly, pipe C is twice as fast as B, so C = 2B = 4A.\n\nWhen all three pipes are working together, they fill the tank in 8 hours. The combined rate of the three pipes is A + B + C. Since they fill 1 tank in 8 hours, their combined rate is 1/8 tanks per hour.\n\nSo we have:\nA + B + C = 1/8\n\nSubstituting B and C in terms of A, we get:\nA + 2A + 4A = 1/8\n7A = 1/8\n\nNow, we solve for A:\nA = (1/8) / 7\nA = 1/56\n\nThis means pipe A fills 1/56 of the tank in one hour. To find out how long it takes for pipe A to fill the entire tank, we take the reciprocal of A's rate:\n\nTime for A to fill the tank = 1 / (1/56) = 56 hours\n\nSo, pipe A alone will take 56 hours to fill the tank."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_612914", "question": "The points $(x, y)$ represented in this table lie on a straight line. The point $(28, t)$ lies on the same line. What is the value of $t?$ \\begin{tabular}{c|c}\n$x$ & $y$ \\\\ \\hline\n1 & 7 \\\\\n3 & 13 \\\\\n5 & 19 \\\\\n\\end{tabular}", "answer": "We can find the slope of the line using the formula $\\dfrac{y_2 - y_1}{x_2 - x_1}$.\nUsing the first two points, we have $\\dfrac{13 - 7}{3 - 1} = \\dfrac{6}{2} = 3$.\nUsing the second and third points, we have $\\dfrac{19 - 13}{5 - 3} = \\dfrac{6}{2} = 3$.\nSince the slope is the same for all pairs of points, we can conclude that all the points lie on the same line.\nTherefore, the point $(28,t)$ also lies on this line, and the value of $t$ can be found by substituting $x=28$ into the equation of the line.\nUsing the first two points, we can determine the equation of the line to be $y = 3x + 4$.\nSubstituting $x=28$, we find $y = 3(28) + 4 = 84 + 4 = 88$.\nTherefore, $t = \\boxed{88}$.The answer is: 88"}
