{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_771382", "question": "Alice had 10 dozens of watermelons. She sold 40% of it yesterday and 1/4 of the remaining today, How many watermelons are left to be sold tomorrow?", "answer": "Alice had 10 dozens of watermelons, which is equal to 10 x 12 = 120 watermelons.\nYesterday, she sold 40% of the watermelons, which is equal to 120 x 0.40 = 48 watermelons.\nSo, Alice has 120 - 48 = 72 watermelons left after selling yesterday.\nToday, she sold 1/4 of the remaining watermelons, which is equal to 72 x 1/4 = 18 watermelons.\nTherefore, there are 72 - 18 = 54 watermelons left to be sold tomorrow.\n#### 54\nThe answer is: 54"}
