{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_781598", "question": "How can I create a HTML page using CSS to continuously scroll text from left to right?", "answer": "To create a HTML page with a CSS animation that continuously scrolls text from left to right, you can use the following code:\n\n```html\n<!DOCTYPE html>\n<html>\n<head>\n<style>\n.marquee {\n    height: 50px;\n    background-color: #f0f0f0;\n    overflow: hidden;\n    position: relative;\n}\n.marquee div {\n    font-size: 30px;\n    position: absolute;\n    width: 100%;\n    height: 100%;\n    margin: 0;\n    line-height: 50px;\n    text-align: center;\n    /* Starting position */\n    transform:translateX(100%);\n    /* Apply animation to this element */\n    animation: leftScroll 10s linear infinite;\n}\n.marquee:hover div{\n    /* Pause animation on hover */\n    animation-play-state: paused;\n}\n/* Animation */\n@keyframes leftScroll {\n    0%   { transform: translateX(100%); }\n    100% { transform: translateX(-100%); }\n}\n</style>\n</head>\n<body>\n    <div class=\"marquee\">\n        <div>The text you want to continuously scroll goes here.</div>\n    </div>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nWith this code, the text will start from the right side (off-screen) and scroll continuously to the left. The `.marquee` class is used to create a container with a fixed height and a background color. The `.marquee div` class is used to style the text element within the container. The `transform: translateX()` property is used to define the starting position of the text, and the `animation` property is used to apply the `leftScroll` animation to the text. The animation moves the text from right to left over a duration of 10 seconds, and it repeats infinitely. Additionally, when the mouse hovers over the container, the animation pauses, and it resumes when the mouse leaves."}
