{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1380874", "question": "Create a shell script to find the size of all folders in a directory, but exclude any folders that have the word \"temp\" in their name. Additionally, exclude any folders that have a total size of more than 100 MB and contain more than 100 files in them.", "answer": "#!/bin/bash\n\n# Specify the directory path\ndirectory=\"/path/to/directory\"\n\n# Loop through all folders in the directory\nfor folder in \"$directory\"/*; do\n    # Check if folder name contains the word \"temp\"\n    if [[ \"$folder\" == *temp* ]]; then\n        continue\n    fi\n    \n    # Get the size of the folder in bytes\n    folder_size=$(du -s \"$folder\" | awk '{print $1}')\n    \n    # Get the count of files in the folder\n    file_count=$(find \"$folder\" -type f | wc -l)\n    \n    # Check if folder size is less than or equal to 100 MB and file count is less than or equal to 100\n    if (( folder_size <= 100000000 && file_count <= 100 )); then\n        # Convert folder size to human-readable format\n        folder_size_hr=$(du -sh \"$folder\" | awk '{print $1}')\n        \n        echo \"Folder: $folder, Size: $folder_size_hr\"\n    fi\ndone"}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1207016", "question": "If 63 percent of a class answered the first question on a certain test correctly, a certain percentage answered the second question on the test correctly, and 20 percent answered neither of the questions correctly. What percent answered the second question correctly if 33 percent answered both correctly?", "answer": "Let's denote the percentage of students who answered the second question correctly as \\( x \\).\n\nWe know that:\n- 63% answered the first question correctly.\n- \\( x \\% \\) answered the second question correctly.\n- 33% answered both questions correctly.\n- 20% answered neither question correctly.\n\nWe can use the principle of inclusion-exclusion to find the percentage of students who answered at least one question correctly. This principle states that to find the union of two sets, we add the sizes of the individual sets and subtract the intersection (the part that is counted twice).\n\nSo, the percentage of students who answered at least one question correctly is:\n\\( 63\\% + x\\% - 33\\% \\)\n\nWe also know that 20% answered neither, so the percentage who answered at least one question correctly is also \\( 100\\% - 20\\% = 80\\% \\).\n\nSetting the two expressions equal to each other, we get:\n\\( 63\\% + x\\% - 33\\% = 80\\% \\)\n\nSolving for \\( x \\):\n\\( x\\% = 80\\% + 33\\% - 63\\% \\)\n\\( x\\% = 113\\% - 63\\% \\)\n\\( x\\% = 50\\% \\)\n\nTherefore, 50 percent of the students answered the second question correctly."}
