{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_4821", "question": "The speeds of three asteroids were compared. Asteroids X-13 and Y-14 were observed for identical durations, while asteroid Z-15 was observed for 2 seconds longer. During its period of observation, asteroid Y-14 traveled three times the distance X-13 traveled, and therefore Y-14 was found to be faster than X-13 by 4000 kilometers per second. Asteroid Z-15 had an identical speed as that of X-13, but because Z-15 was observed for a longer period, it traveled five times the distance X-13 traveled during X-13's inspection. How many kilometers did asteroid X-13 travel during its observation?", "answer": "Let's denote the speed of asteroid X-13 as \\( V_{X} \\) and the time it was observed as \\( T \\). Since asteroid Y-14 traveled three times the distance of X-13 in the same time and was 4000 km/s faster, we can write the following equations:\n\nFor asteroid X-13:\n\\[ \\text{Distance}_{X} = V_{X} \\cdot T \\]\n\nFor asteroid Y-14:\n\\[ \\text{Distance}_{Y} = (V_{X} + 4000) \\cdot T \\]\nGiven that:\n\\[ \\text{Distance}_{Y} = 3 \\cdot \\text{Distance}_{X} \\]\n\nSo we can equate the two expressions for distance:\n\\[ (V_{X} + 4000) \\cdot T = 3 \\cdot V_{X} \\cdot T \\]\n\nNow, let's solve for \\( V_{X} \\):\n\\[ V_{X} \\cdot T + 4000 \\cdot T = 3 \\cdot V_{X} \\cdot T \\]\n\\[ 4000 \\cdot T = 3 \\cdot V_{X} \\cdot T - V_{X} \\cdot T \\]\n\\[ 4000 \\cdot T = 2 \\cdot V_{X} \\cdot T \\]\n\\[ V_{X} = \\frac{4000 \\cdot T}{2 \\cdot T} \\]\n\\[ V_{X} = 2000 \\text{ km/s} \\]\n\nNow, asteroid Z-15, which has the same speed as X-13, traveled for \\( T + 2 \\) seconds and covered five times the distance of X-13. So we have:\n\\[ \\text{Distance}_{Z} = V_{X} \\cdot (T + 2) \\]\nGiven that:\n\\[ \\text{Distance}_{Z} = 5 \\cdot \\text{Distance}_{X} \\]\n\nWe can write:\n\\[ 2000 \\cdot (T + 2) = 5 \\cdot 2000 \\cdot T \\]\n\\[ 2000 \\cdot T + 4000 = 10000 \\cdot T \\]\n\\[ 4000 = 10000 \\cdot T - 2000 \\cdot T \\]\n\\[ 4000 = 8000 \\cdot T \\]\n\\[ T = \\frac{4000}{8000} \\]\n\\[ T = 0.5 \\text{ seconds} \\]\n\nNow we can find the distance traveled by X-13:\n\\[ \\text{Distance}_{X} = V_{X} \\cdot T \\]\n\\[ \\text{Distance}_{X} = 2000 \\cdot 0.5 \\]\n\\[ \\text{Distance}_{X} = 1000 \\text{ km} \\]\n\nSo, asteroid X-13 traveled 1000 kilometers during its observation."}
