{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_815110", "question": "An equilateral triangle has a perimeter of 24 cm. What is the length of one side of the triangle?", "answer": "An equilateral triangle has three equal sides. To find the length of one side, we can divide the perimeter by the number of sides.\n\nPerimeter = 24 cm\nNumber of sides = 3\n\nLength of one side = Perimeter / Number of sides = 24 cm / 3 = 8 cm\n\nThe length of one side of the equilateral triangle is 8 cm."}
