{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_400648", "question": "A round-robin tennis tournament consists of each player playing every other player exactly once.  How many matches will be held during an 8-person round-robin tennis tournament?", "answer": "In a round-robin tournament, each player plays against every other player exactly once.\nSince there are 8 players, each player will play 7 matches (against the other 7 players).\nHowever, we have counted each match twice (once for each player involved).\nTherefore, we need to divide the total number of matches by 2 to get the actual number of matches played.\nSo the number of matches in an 8-person round-robin tournament is $\\frac{8 \\cdot 7}{2} = \\boxed{28}$.\nThe answer is: 28"}
