{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1010244", "question": "The speed of a car is 20 km in the first hour and 30 km in the second hour. What is the average speed of the car?", "answer": "To find the average speed of the car, we need to divide the total distance traveled by the total time taken.\n\nIn the first hour, the car travels 20 km, and in the second hour, it travels 30 km. So the total distance traveled is:\n\n20 km + 30 km = 50 km\n\nThe total time taken is 2 hours (1 hour for the first hour and 1 hour for the second hour).\n\nNow we can calculate the average speed:\n\nAverage speed = Total distance / Total time\nAverage speed = 50 km / 2 hours\nAverage speed = 25 km/h\n\nSo the average speed of the car is 25 km/h."}
