{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_520038", "question": "The graph of the line $x+y=b$ is a perpendicular bisector of the line segment from $(0,3)$ to $(6,9)$. What is the value of b?", "answer": "If the line $x+y=b$ is the perpendicular bisector of the segment from $(0,3)$ to $(6,9)$, it must pass through the midpoint of this segment.  The midpoint is: $$\\left(\\frac{0+6}{2},\\frac{3+9}{2}\\right)=(3,6)$$This point lies on the line $x+y=b$, so we must have $3+6=b\\Rightarrow b=\\boxed{9}$. The answer is 9"}
