{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_537734", "question": "Evaluate $\\log_\\frac{1}{3}9$.", "answer": "We want to find the exponent to which $\\frac{1}{3}$ must be raised to obtain 9.\nIn other words, we want to solve the equation $\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^x = 9$.\nWe can rewrite 9 as $\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^{-2}$.\nSo, we have $\\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^x = \\left(\\frac{1}{3}\\right)^{-2}$.\nSince the bases are equal, the exponents must be equal.\nTherefore, $x = -2$.\nSo, $\\log_\\frac{1}{3}9 = \\boxed{-2}$.\nThe answer is: -2"}
