{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_358683", "question": "A rhombus has diagonals of lengths 10 cm and 30 cm. What is the area of the rhombus?", "answer": "The area of a rhombus can be calculated using the formula:\n\nArea = (d1 * d2) / 2\n\nwhere d1 and d2 are the lengths of the diagonals.\n\nGiven that the diagonals are 10 cm and 30 cm, we can plug these values into the formula:\n\nArea = (10 cm * 30 cm) / 2\nArea = (300 cm²) / 2\nArea = 150 cm²\n\nSo, the area of the rhombus is 150 square centimeters."}
{"id": "general_infinity_instruct_2300_1400075", "question": "A couple who own an appliance store discover that if they advertise a certain sales discount on every item in the store, at the end of one month the number of total items sold increases by 12%. Their gross income from sales for one month increases by 0.8%. What is the sales discount percentage they offered?", "answer": "Let's denote the original price of an item as \\( P \\), the number of items sold originally as \\( N \\), and the sales discount percentage as \\( D \\). \n\nThe original gross income from sales, without any discount, would be:\n\\[ \\text{Original Gross Income} = P \\times N \\]\n\nAfter applying the discount, the price of each item becomes \\( P \\times (1 - \\frac{D}{100}) \\), and the number of items sold increases by 12%, so the new number of items sold is \\( N \\times 1.12 \\).\n\nThe new gross income from sales, with the discount, is:\n\\[ \\text{New Gross Income} = P \\times (1 - \\frac{D}{100}) \\times N \\times 1.12 \\]\n\nWe are given that the new gross income is 0.8% higher than the original gross income, so we can set up the following equation:\n\\[ P \\times (1 - \\frac{D}{100}) \\times N \\times 1.12 = P \\times N \\times (1 + 0.008) \\]\n\nNow, we can simplify and solve for \\( D \\):\n\\[ (1 - \\frac{D}{100}) \\times 1.12 = 1 + 0.008 \\]\n\\[ 1.12 - \\frac{1.12D}{100} = 1.008 \\]\n\\[ 1.12 - 1.008 = \\frac{1.12D}{100} \\]\n\\[ 0.112 = \\frac{1.12D}{100} \\]\n\\[ D = \\frac{0.112 \\times 100}{1.12} \\]\n\\[ D = \\frac{11.2}{1.12} \\]\n\\[ D = 10 \\]\n\nTherefore, the sales discount percentage they offered is 10%."}
